               <p>RICHARD CULVERWELL. I am a <rs id="t18321018-221-viclabel1231" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-221-victim1926 t18321018-221-viclabel1231"></join>, and live in<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183210180096"></xptr>
                  <placeName id="t18321018-221-crimeloc1232">Great Marylebone-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-221-crimeloc1232" type="placeName" value="Great Marylebone-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-221-crimeloc1232" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-221-off1229 t18321018-221-crimeloc1232"></join>. I lost this piece of cloth from my shop - I saw the prisoner, who was a stranger, turning out of my shop; I had not left my cutting-board five minutes; the prisoner was quite a stranger - I did not see him come in; I called to him, but he would not stop - I left my chair, and followed him; I called to him, and then he would not stop - I walked after him; when he got about thirty yards he began to run; I called Stop thief! a butterman put his basket down, and tried to stop him, but could not - he turned Bulstrode-street; I was close after him, and saw him throw down the cloth, with the intention of throwing it down an area, but he could not - I took it up, the Policeman brought him back, and took the cloth.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-221-person1927">
                  JAMES 
                  FORD
